ity-dwelling older population with MCI, approximately 30\% and 18\% reverted to NC for 5~years and 10~years, respectively. The prevention and proper management of lifestyle-related diseases and promotion of healthy lifestyle behaviors may play a crucial role in facilitating reversion to NC in older individuals with MCI.},
